  BIDVEST Wits have officially confirmed the signing of Cameroonian striker Eva Nga. The 26-year-old joins Wits from Mozambican side Clube de Desportos da Costa do Sol. The striker is expected to ease pressure on Gift Motupa who has been the man leading Wits attack since the season started. Wits coach Gavin Hunt admitted that the team needed a striker. “I’ve been watching Eva for some time now and I like what I see," said hunt. "He was the top goal scorer in the Mozambican league so let’s see what transpires from here.”Wits COO, Jonathan Schloss had this to say about their new striker. “We’re obviously delighted to welcome Eva. Schloss added: "He’s an exciting striker whom we believe will thrive in our club environment. He certainly gives our coach Gavin Hunt additional ammunition upfront and we have every belief that he can emulate the form shown in Mozambique,” Nga finished as top scorer in Mozambique with 24 goals and landed the award for the Moçambola Player of the Season as he helped Cosa do Sol clinch another league title. 